quixotic
	adj. exceedingly idealistic
succinct
	adj. briefly and clearly expressed
recalcitrant
	adj. having an obstinately uncooperative attitude toward authority or discipline
onus
	n. used to refer to something that is one's duty or responsibility
exegesis
	n. critical explanation or interpretation of a text, esp of scripture
hidebound
	adj. unwilling or unable to change because of tradition or convention
